dialogue.String: It was somewhere around here.1�
Aaaaaaaaa!1�
This!? You were worried about a funguarrr!?1�
No, I was...1�
B-behind you!1�
This outcropping is the perfect spot to begin!1�
(To think that this technopedia my damned father gave me when I was ten would actually prove of use...unfathomable.)1�
(Normal kids get toys or sweets for their birthdays. Not me...but here I am now, all because of this little book.)1�
Gah! For the love of...you gave me a good scare!1�
How do you address him?Midras �[./?]Junior �[./?]1�
Who are you, and how do you know my name!?1�
Further, what're you doing all the way out here?1�
Hey now! What gives you the right to call me ��Junior��!? I hate when people call me that!1�
I've got a real name, you know. ��Midras.��1�
How did you even know that nickname, anyway?1�
Oh, now I get it. That cursed Tarutaru told you.1�
Who are you, exactly?1�
An adventurer from the Middle Lands. That must make you a pioneer.1�
You must have gotten here by the waypoints then. Pshaw.1�
Not all of us took the easy way, you know. When I first came here, I had to take a ship across the tumultuous Sea of Zafmlug. Now just about anyone can make the journey.1�
No seasickness, no lack of food, no worry about being capsized by some deep-sea denizen. You should count your blessings.1�
I suppose you didn't come here to be lectured.1�
However, while we're on the topic, those waypoints you use were developed right here in Adoulin, by the Inventors' Coalition.1�
The wonders they come up with day by day never cease to amaze me.1�
I know making the trip here was the right decision--difficult though it was--after seeing all they do. I've learned more here in a week than I could in Jeuno in years.1�
...Is that so? Amchuchu herself? She's always worried about how I'm holding up.1�
Sorry that you came all this way, but no matter how much I want to go back, I can't yet. Things are more...difficult than I anticipated.1�
Aha! That gives me an idea. Being an adventurer means you can use the waypoints, can't you?1�
Isn't that right, �[Mr./Ms.]..1�
What was your name again?1�
Ah, yes,  .1�
Allow me to introduce myself properly: I'm Midras. Charmed, I'm sure.1�
Now then, if Amchuchu is waiting, then I can't really dillydally here any longer.1�
, I know we've just met, but I need you to do something for me. Go to Bastok and get a certain concoction from an inventor named Cid.1�
I shouldn't talk about him like some stranger, because he is my father, after all...1�
Oh? Amchuchu already told you that?1�
I'm sure you must know all about me by now. <Snort>1�
(I'd give my life savings to have her keep her trap shut.)1�
Anyway, I need that concoction from pops to prepare my own explosive compound.1�
I ran out, you see. It's my own fault for not properly checking my supplies.1�
What I need you to get is a bit on the rare side, and it would take days to find some here in Adoulin. But pops has some in his workshop. Of that I can be sure.1�
I know you'll help me out with this.1�
How about it?Promise to go to Bastok.Not with that attitude!1�
I knew I could count on you.1�
The compound names are a bit technical, so here...take this list so you don't have to remember it all. Give it to my old man, would you kindly?1�
Thanks a bunch,  !1�
You're kidding, right?1�
I know you'll come around. After all, this is the first step in helping Adoulin feed its populace!1�
How do you address him?Midras �[./?]Junior �[./?]1�
Well, well, look who the Mithra dragged in.1�
This is unbelievable. I told you, my name is MID-RAS.1�
Can't find any good help around here. I bet you didn't even bring back what I requested.1�
You hand over 3����.�
Oh ho, you actually did it. Color me impressed. Now, to just do a little fiddling around...1�
Excellent. This should serve perfectly.1�
What are you, scared? Get back over here.1�
Marvelous!1�
Not all explosives are about making things burst into flames. Sometimes a more delicate approach is required. But I suppose I can't fault an amateur such as yourself for not knowing.1�
You see, even though this explosion was rather tame, it helped me excavate exactly what I need.1�
It's called a ��chemical reaction.��1�
This substance is the future,  !1�
Accept it or be left in the dust!1�
But I'll leave the lessons for when you've become a bit more refined.1�
Damn, I forgot Amchuchu was waiting for me.1�
, there's one more task I have for you. Bring this back to the Inventors' Coalition for me.1�
I've got a bit more preparation to do here.1�
(Omega, give me your report.)1�
(This is Omega. I have successfully found employ at the Inventors' Coalition in Adoulin and am currently working to gather information about their unique technologies.)1�
(I am also in the process of collecting intel about the other coalitions, groups, and organizations in the nation. I will submit a full briefing once I have more to share.)1�
(However, I have run into difficulties finding reliable sources regarding these runic technologies and the underlying structure behind geomancy.)1�
(...Understood. Don't concern yourself with the latter--many other agents are already in place. Proceed with your current mission. We await further details.)1�
(Isn't that Midras, Amchuchu's little lackey...?)1�
(And isn't he also the technician dispatched from the Middle Lands?)1�
(��Omega��... this whole deal sounds very secretive. And Gratzigg doesn't like secrets.)1�
(I must return to headquarters and apprise him of the situation...)1�
